```

**The flow:** browse â†’ add to cart â†’ checkout creates a `pending` order â†’ redirect to the payment provider's sandbox page â†’ on "Pay", the provider posts a **signed event to `POST /webhook`** server-side â†’ the webhook verifies the HMAC signature, marks the order `paid` (idempotently), and decrements stock. Users see `My Orders`; admins see every order at `/admin/orders` with status filters.

**Payments:** Default `mock` provider is fully self-contained (no keys, runs offline) but behaves like a real provider â€” it calls back our own `/webhook` out-of-band rather than marking paid on the browser redirect. Setting `PAYMENT_PROVIDER=stripe` + Stripe test keys uses real Stripe Checkout against the *same* webhook endpoint.

## How to run it locally (port 5089)

```powershell
python -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install -r requirements.txt
python app.py
```

Open <http://localhost:5089>. The SQLite DB, demo products, and admin account are auto-seeded on first launch.

