## Security controls (mapped to your requirements)

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| SQL injection | Every query uses `?` placeholders (`db.py`, `models.py`) â€” no string-built SQL |
| Password hashing | **bcrypt**, salted, in `models.py` |
| Input validation | WTForms validators on all fields (email, length, quantity range) |
| XSS | Jinja2 autoescaping + strict CSP (no `unsafe-inline`) |
| CSRF | Flask-WTF tokens on every POST; only `/webhook` is exempt â€” authenticated by HMAC signature instead |
| Access control / IDOR | Orders always fetched scoped to the owning user; admin gated by `admin_required` |
| Secure cookies | `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` (when `SESSION_COOKIE_SECURE=1`) |
| Security headers | CSP, `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `Referrer-Policy`, `Permissions-Policy`, HSTS on HTTPS |
| No error leakage | Custom 400/403/404/500 pages; internals logged, never returned; debug off by default |
| No hardcoded secrets | All read from env/`.env`; ephemeral dev fallback with a warning |
| Payment integrity | Order totals computed server-side from DB prices; webhook requires valid signature + replay window |

